22. Technical Stack and Design Summary

Technical Stack Table

Component	Technology	Description
Frontend Core	React 19 & Vite	High-speed rendering with the new use API and Action hooks.
State	Zustand	Multi-slice store (usePortfolioStore, useRiskStore, useMacroStore).
Event Bus	Kafka (Redpanda)	Sub-5ms latency for internal MarketEvent and SignalEvent streams.
Graph DB	Neo4j	Correlation mapping using LIQUIDITY_SOURCE and INFLATION_HEDGE edges.
Time Series	Postgres (TimescaleDB)	Forensic storage of OHLCV data and UnifiedActivityService logs.
Visuals	D3.js & Canvas	60 FPS rendering of Monte Carlo paths and Yield Curves.
Animation	Framer Motion	Smooth transitions for glassmorphism window chrome and gauges.

Design Philosophy

The UI implements a Glassmorphism / High-Fidelity HUD aesthetic. All widget containers utilize a 20px backdrop-filter: blur() and 70% opacity background fill, maintaining a 7:1 contrast ratio for professional readability. This serves the "Yellowstone Wolf" strategy by allowing the warden to focus on primary execution tasks while keeping "ghost" visibility of background telemetry and agent heartbeats in the periphery.

Final Expansion Takeaways

1. Systemic Evolution: The platform successfully transitions from a tactical terminal to a macro-governance engine for total financial homeostasis.
2. Cognitive Decoupling: By automating the regulation of the "Enough" metric, the human operator is freed from the noise of market oscillations.
3. Institutional Durability: The integration of the "Fort Knox" legal boundary and inheritance protocols ensures the financial ecosystem survives both market shocks and time.
